🔹 What is Spring Web MVC?

Spring Web MVC is a framework for building web applications that separates:

Model → Data (Java objects, DB data)

View → UI (JSP, HTML, Thymeleaf)

Controller → Business logic (handles requests)

🔹 Architecture (Flow)
4
Flow Explanation:

Client sends request (browser)

Request goes to DispatcherServlet (front controller)

DispatcherServlet calls Controller

Controller processes logic & returns Model + View

ViewResolver maps view name to actual UI (JSP/HTML)

Response sent back to client

🔹 Key Components
1. DispatcherServlet (Front Controller)

Core of Spring MVC

Handles all incoming requests

2. Controller

Written using @Controller

Handles request mapping

@Controller
public class MyController {

    @RequestMapping("/hello")
    public String greet() {
        return "hello";
    }
}
3. Model

Holds data to send to view

model.addAttribute("name", "Rishav");
4. View

JSP / Thymeleaf / HTML page

Displays data

5. ViewResolver

Maps logical view → actual file

Example:

spring.mvc.view.prefix=/WEB-INF/views/
spring.mvc.view.suffix=.jsp
🔹 Annotations Used
Annotation	Purpose
@Controller	Marks class as controller
@RestController	Controller + JSON response
@RequestMapping	Maps URL
@GetMapping	GET request
@PostMapping	POST request
@ResponseBody	Returns data directly
🔹 Example (Real-World)

👉 Login Form

User enters username/password

Controller validates

Model stores user data

View shows dashboard or error page

🔹 Spring MVC vs Spring Boot
Feature	Spring MVC	Spring Boot
Configuration	Manual (XML/Java)	Auto-config
Setup	Complex	Easy
Server	External Tomcat	Embedded Tomcat
🔹 Advantages

✔ Separation of concerns
✔ Flexible & scalable
✔ Easy integration with DB, Security, REST
✔ Supports REST APIs

