explain web mvc archgitecture

Spring Web MVC architecture is all about how a request travels from the browser to the server and back with a response, using the MVC pattern.

🔷 Spring Web MVC Architecture
4
🔶 Core Idea (MVC Pattern)

Model → Data (Java objects, DB)

View → UI (JSP / HTML / Thymeleaf)

Controller → Handles request & logic

🔷 Step-by-Step Flow (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥)
1️⃣ Client Request

User sends request from browser
👉 Example: http://localhost:8080/home

2️⃣ DispatcherServlet (Front Controller)

Central component of Spring Framework

Receives all requests

👉 Think of it like a manager that decides what to do next.

3️⃣ Handler Mapping

Finds which controller should handle request

👉 Example:

@GetMapping("/home")
4️⃣ Controller Execution

Controller processes request

Calls service / DB if needed

@Controller
public class HomeController {

    @GetMapping("/home")
    public String getHome(Model model) {
        model.addAttribute("msg", "Welcome Rishav");
        return "home";
    }
}
5️⃣ Model Creation

Data is stored in Model

👉 Example:

model.addAttribute("msg", "Welcome Rishav");
6️⃣ View Resolver

Converts logical view name → actual file

👉 Example:

home → /WEB-INF/views/home.jsp
7️⃣ View Rendering

JSP/HTML page gets data and renders UI

8️⃣ Response to Client

Final HTML page is sent back to browser

🔷 Components Summary
Component	Role
DispatcherServlet	Handles all requests
HandlerMapping	Maps URL → Controller
Controller	Business logic
Model	Holds data
ViewResolver	Finds view
View	Displays data
